            <h2>üîí Overview</h2>
            <p>DearFixer is an AI-powered email enhancement tool that helps users improve their email communication. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your data.</p>

            <h2>üìä Data Collection</h2>

            <h3>What We Collect:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Google Account Information:</strong> Email address, name, and profile picture (via Google OAuth)</li>
                <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Number of email polish requests and subscription status</li>
                <li><strong>Email Content:</strong> Only the text you explicitly select and choose to polish (processed temporarily)</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>What We DON'T Collect:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>We do <strong>NOT</strong> store your email content permanently</li>
                <li>We do <strong>NOT</strong> access emails you don't explicitly select</li>
                <li>We do <strong>NOT</strong> track your browsing outside of email polishing</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>üéØ Data Usage</h2>

            <h3>How We Use Your Data:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Google account info for login and subscription management</li>
                <li><strong>AI Processing:</strong> Selected email text is sent to OpenAI for enhancement (not stored)</li>
                <li><strong>Usage Tracking:</strong> Monitor your polish requests for subscription limits</li>
                <li><strong>Payment Processing:</strong> Stripe handles payments (we don't store payment info)</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>üîê Data Storage and Security</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Temporary Processing:</strong> Email content is processed in real-time and not stored</li>
                <li><strong>Secure Transmission:</strong> All data transmitted over HTTPS</li>
                <li><strong>AWS Infrastructure:</strong> Usage data stored securely on AWS with encryption</li>
                <li><strong>No Third-Party Sharing:</strong> Your data is never sold or shared with third parties</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>ü§ù Third-Party Services</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>OpenAI:</strong> Processes your email text for AI enhancement</li>
                <li><strong>Google OAuth:</strong> Handles authentication</li>
                <li><strong>Stripe:</strong> Processes payments securely</li>
                <li><strong>AWS:</strong> Stores usage and subscription data</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>‚öñÔ∏è Your Rights</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Data Access:</strong> Contact us to access your stored data</li>
                <li><strong>Account Deletion:</strong> You have the right to delete your account and all associated data</li>
                <li><strong>Data Portability:</strong> Request a copy of your data in a portable format</li>
                <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> Uninstall the extension to stop all data collection</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="highlight">
                <h3>üóëÔ∏è How to Delete Your Account</h3>
                <p><strong>Self-Service Account Deletion:</strong></p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open the DearFixer extension</li>
                    <li>Click "Account Settings"</li>
                    <li>Select "Delete Account"</li>
                    <li>Confirm deletion - this will permanently remove all your data and cancel any active subscriptions</li>
                </ol>
                
                <p><strong>What Gets Deleted:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Your Google account association</li>
                    <li>Usage history and statistics</li>
                    <li>Subscription information (active subscriptions will be cancelled)</li>
                    <li>All personally identifiable information</li>
                </ul>
                
                <p><strong>Note:</strong> Account deletion is permanent and cannot be undone.</p>
            </div>

